{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀήρ</b>, ἀέρος, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus ἀήρ, ἠέρος\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>nominative</i> ἠήρ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 6, +others, 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “ὀξέων νούσων θεραπευτικόν” 2.3\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Aeolic dialect</i> αὐήρ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.52\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Doric dialect</i> ἀβήρ (i.e. ἀϜήρ) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus:— _feminine_ in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus and 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus (except “Op.” 549), 5th c.BC: Anaxagoras Philosophus cited in 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Sensu” 30; from Hdt downwards _masculine_ (8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.776, 8.50, “hymnus ad Cererem” 383 cannot be quoted for the _masculine_ usage, since there πουλύς and βαθύς need not be _masculine_):—in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus and 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] always <b>mist, haze</b>, not (as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Aristarchus Grammaticus)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] <b>lower air</b> (opposed to αἰθήρ, which see); [ἐλάτη] μακροτάτη πεφυυῖα δι᾽ ἠέρος αἰθέρ᾽ ἵκανεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.288, compare 5th c.BC: Anaxagoras Philosophus 1, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 264sq.; περὶ δ᾽ ἠέρα πουλὺν ἔχευεν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.776, compare 3.381, 8.50; ἠέρα μὲν σκέδας εν καὶ ἀπῶσεν ὀμί χλην 17.649; τρὶς δ᾽ ἠέρα τύψε βαθεῖαν 20.446\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; rare in Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus [prev. cited] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> later, generally, <b>air</b>, Anaxim.1, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 17.18, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 87, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 187, 694, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρὸς τὸν ἀέρα διατρίβειν in <b>the open air</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 198, compare 3rd c.BC: Teles Philosophus p.11.3 H., 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Anach.” 24; τὸν ἀέρ᾽ ἕλκειν καθαρόν 5th c.BC: Philyllius Comicus 20, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 119; ἔσπασας τὸν ἀ. τὸν κοινόν 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 531.7; ἀέρα δέρειν NT.1Cor.9.26; εἰς ἀέρᾳ λαλεῖν [prev. work] 14.9:—in _plural_, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 98c, 98d\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>climates</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” at Title Page, cf. Men.Rh.p.383 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of mephitic <b>exhalations</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 5.4.5. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> personified, ὦ δέσποτ᾽ ἄναξ ἀμέτρητ᾽ Ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 264; Ἀ. ὃν ἄν τις ὀνομάσειε καὶ Δία 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 91.4, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Diphilus Comicus 126.6. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>hot-air room</b> in baths, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 11.14. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>volume</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “*Stereom.” 57, +others \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> a pigment, <b>sky-blue</b> or <b>grey</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Aut.” 28.3\">Refs</a>]. [ᾱ, except in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 642, 1st c.AD(?): Pseudo-Phocylidea [108].]\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0109","accentedUnicode":"ἀήρ","shortDef":"a